<paragraph blockId="1.[151,943,1051,1078]" box="[151,943,1051,1078]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,943,1051,1078]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,943,1051,1078]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
Key to the Indomalayan species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Forster, 1869" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1869" box="[586,943,1051,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Gnathochorisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[586,772,1051,1078]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Gnathochorisis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Forster, A." box="[779,943,1051,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" pagination="135 - 221" refId="ref4423" refString="Forster, A. (1869) Synopsis der Familien und Gattungen der Ichneumonen. Verhandlungen des Naturhistorischen Vereins der Preussischen Rheinlande und Westfalens, 25, 135 - 221." type="journal article" year="1869">Förster, 1869</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="415" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1120,1406]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
1. Second metasomal tergite as long as wide posteriorly; fore wing with closed areolet; area superomedia longer than wide; propodeum without anterior section of lateromedian longitudinal carinae; first flagellomere 5.3 × as long as wide; face, frontal orbits and pronotum yellow; body slender........................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Humala" authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2021" box="[1244,1436,1179,1201]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Gnathochorisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis box="[1244,1354,1179,1200]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">G. malaisei</emphasis>
Humala
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1120,1406]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
– Second metasomal tergite clearly transverse (
<figureCitation box="[663,739,1208,1230]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); fore wing without areolet (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1092,1208,1230]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-178@3.[164,1423,489,1955]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) metasoma, lateral view; B) metasoma, dorsal view; C) wings." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
); area superomedia distinctly wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[329,401,1237,1260]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
); propodeum with anterior section of lateromedian longitudinal carinae (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1173,1237,1260]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
); first flagellomere 4.3–4.7 × as long as wide; face, frontal orbits and pronotum fuscous (
<figureCitation box="[814,952,1267,1289]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Figs 1A, B, D</figureCitation>
); body more robust....................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1120,1406]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
2. Area superomedia 1.25 × as wide as long; lower face smooth medially; clypeus 1.6 × as wide as high; hind femur 3.0 × as long as wide................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Humala" authorityName="Humala. Apart" authorityYear="2021" box="[1277,1436,1325,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Gnathochorisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leleji">
<emphasis box="[1277,1354,1325,1347]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">G. leleji</emphasis>
Humala
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1120,1406]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
– Area superomedia 1.8 × as wide as long (
<figureCitation box="[625,697,1355,1377]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
); lower face transversely striate medially (
<figureCitation box="[1108,1182,1355,1377]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); clypeus 2.0 × as wide as high (
<figureCitation box="[282,356,1384,1406]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-116@2.[164,1423,342,1808]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gnathochorisis jasoni sp. nov., holotype, female A) habitus, lateral view; B) head, anterior view; C) head, dorsal view; D) head &amp; mesosoma, lateral view; E) mesosoma, dorsal view; F) propodeum, dorsal view." pageId="1" pageNumber="415">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); hind femur 3.6 × as long as wide................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ranjith &amp; Humala &amp; Priyadarsanan, 2022" authorityName="Ranjith &amp; Humala &amp; Priyadarsanan" authorityYear="2022" box="[1266,1354,1384,1406]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Gnathochorisis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jasoni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1266,1354,1384,1406]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">G. jasoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1360,1436,1384,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,1384,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="415" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
